remarks: A mapping (first hypothesis) that is one-to-one (second hypothesis) implies its domain is dominated by its codomain.  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 20-May-2013.)
statement:
dom2d.1 $e |- ( ph -> ( x e. A -> C e. B ) ) $.
dom2d.2 $e |- ( ph -> ( ( x e. A /\ y e. A ) -> ( C = D <-> x = y ) ) ) $.
dom3d.3 $e |- ( ph -> A e. V ) $.
dom3d.4 $e |- ( ph -> B e. W ) $.
dom3d $p |- ( ph -> A ~<_ B ) $.
